<subSubSection box="[198,1059,450,476]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,551]" box="[198,1059,450,476]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,331,450,476]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is named for its resemblance to braconid wasps.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,551]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,330,487,513]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Discussion</emphasis>
. This species is similar to the next species, but larger and darker; additional differences are given under that species. The 
<typeStatus box="[501,602,525,551]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">paratype</typeStatus>
measures 
<quantity box="[725,829,525,551]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.45" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="8.45">8.45 mm</quantity>
in length.
</paragraph>
